  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API. Flag filter is an endpoint filter; runs in the standard pipeline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint authorization runs FIRST. Feature flag does NOT bypass authorization. An unauthorized caller hitting a disabled feature still gets 401 (auth check wins). Verified by test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-009">Per-Action kill-switch cache uses `IDistributedCache` (Redis). Cache keys versioned with Action rowversion. 30-second TTL for fast propagation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Flag service + options registered via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension. Module total ≤15 non-framework registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Feature flag service is a cross-cutting infrastructure concern — placed under `Infrastructure/FeatureFlags/`, NOT inside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`. The service surfaces booleans only; no AE internal types leak.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">**PRIMARY**. Typed options class for flags. Startup validation. 503 ProblemDetails on disabled. Same flag checked in endpoints AND async handlers. Flags NEVER bypass authorization. Documented defaults + environment behavior for every flag.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">503 response uses ProblemDetails (RFC 7807) with `status: 503`, `title: "Service Unavailable"`, `detail: "Action Engine /run is currently disabled by feature flag"` (or per-Action equivalent).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages — typed options + IDistributedCache are in framework.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF, publish-size unchanged, no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per-Action kill switch is the operational lever for incident response. 30-second worst-case propagation. Documented in `notes/decisions/feature-flags-inventory.md`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

