    <step order="2">Create `Configuration/ActionEngineFeatureFlags.cs` per ADR-018 typed-options conventions. Fields per `&lt;goal&gt;` section. Add `[Required]` validation attributes. Register via `services.Configure&lt;ActionEngineFeatureFlags&gt;(config.GetSection("ActionEngineFeatureFlags"))` + `services.AddOptions&lt;ActionEngineFeatureFlags&gt;().ValidateDataAnnotations().ValidateOnStart()`.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Infrastructure/FeatureFlags/IFeatureFlagService.cs` + `FeatureFlagService.cs`. Methods: `bool IsActionInvocationEnabled()` (reads typed options); `bool IsScheduledDispatchEnabled()` (reads typed options); `Task&lt;bool&gt; IsActionEnabledAsync(Guid actionId, CancellationToken ct)` (combines BOTH layers: global + per-Action). Implement per-Action check with `IDistributedCache` (Redis) caching the Action's `governance.killSwitchActive` field with key `action-engine:killswitch:{actionId}` + Action rowversion suffix per ADR-009. 30-second TTL.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `Infrastructure/FeatureFlags/FeatureFlagFilter.cs` implementing `IEndpointFilter`. Constructor takes a flag-name string. Checks `IFeatureFlagService.IsActionInvocationEnabled()` (or the named flag); on false → `Results.Problem(statusCode: 503, title: "Service Unavailable", detail: "...", type: "https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-6.6.4")`. Order in the pipeline: AFTER auth (so 401 wins over 503 for the unauthorized-and-disabled case), BEFORE rate limiter, BEFORE resource authorization filter.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `ActionEndpoints.cs`: add `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;FeatureFlagFilter&gt;()` (configured with the `ai-action-invocation` flag) to every Action endpoint. For the `/run` endpoint specifically, ALSO add an additional check INSIDE the handler (or as a late endpoint filter that runs after resource resolution) calling `IFeatureFlagService.IsActionEnabledAsync(actionId, ct)` — if false, return 503 with detail referencing the Action id.</step>
    <step order="6">Add admin endpoints to `ActionEndpoints.cs`:
      - `POST /api/ai/actions/{actionId}/admin/disable` — requires `ActionEngine.Admin` role. Body: `{ reason?: string }`. Updates Action Definition's `governance.killSwitchActive = true` in Dataverse via the facade. Evicts the cache key. Emits `action_engine.killswitch.toggled` App Insights event.
      - `POST /api/ai/actions/{actionId}/admin/enable` — symmetrical inverse.
      Both endpoints use a dedicated `AdminAuthorizationFilter` that asserts `User.IsInRole("ActionEngine.Admin")`. On role miss → 403 ProblemDetails.</step>
    <step order="7">Edit `Services/Jobs/ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.cs` (from task 042): in the `HandleAsync` pipeline, check `IFeatureFlagService.IsScheduledDispatchEnabled()` + `IsActionEnabledAsync(actionId, ct)` early. If either false → return `JobOutcome.Skipped`. This satisfies ADR-018's "same flag checked in both endpoints and async handlers" binding rule.</step>
    <step order="8">DI registration: register `IFeatureFlagService` + `FeatureFlagService` as scoped in `AddActionEngineModule()`. Register the options. Confirm total non-framework registrations ≤15 (ADR-010).</step>
    <step order="9">Edit `appsettings.json` to add `ActionEngineFeatureFlags` section with defaults (all true). Edit `appsettings.Development.json` to inherit defaults. Write `notes/decisions/feature-flags-inventory.md` documenting EVERY flag: name, default, environment behavior, who can change it, how propagation works. Write `notes/decisions/admin-roles.md` documenting the new `ActionEngine.Admin` role and how to assign it.</step>
    <step order="9.3">Write integration tests at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/ActionEngine/FeatureFlagIntegrationTests.cs`:
      (a) Global `ActionInvocationEnabled = false` → /run returns 503 with ProblemDetails;
      (b) Per-Action kill switch on → /run returns 503 with detail referencing the Action id;
      (c) ADR-018 binding test: global flag OFF + unauthorized caller → 401 (auth wins over flag — flag does NOT bypass authorization);
      (d) Admin disable endpoint requires `ActionEngine.Admin` role — regular caller gets 403; admin gets 200 + cache eviction + App Insights event;
      (e) After admin disable, /run returns 503; after admin enable, /run returns 200 (or 401/403 if caller's auth fails on /run — orthogonal to the flag check);
      (f) Cache propagation: an admin disable in one BFF instance is visible in another instance within 30 seconds (test with two `IDistributedCache`-sharing instances or simulate via cache eviction).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the new options + service + filter + admin endpoints + appsettings; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (auth not bypassed), ADR-009 (Redis-cached flag with versioning), ADR-018 (typed options + 503 ProblemDetails + same flag in handler + documented), ADR-019 (503 returns ProblemDetails). Re-run `dotnet build` and integration tests.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 045 ✅. Verify it unblocks tasks 060, 061, 062, 063 (the integration test phase). Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
